<h1>Company introduction</h1>
<h3>WELCOME TO THE PASSENGER RAIL AGENCY OF SOUTH AFRICA - METRORAIL GAUTENG</h3>

<p>The Passenger Rail Agency of South Africa (PRASA) Metrorail Gauteng is the agency of the Department of Transport responsible for the provision of commuter rail services in Gauteng. It has custodianship of all commuter rail assets.</p>
<p>Metrorail Gauteng as an operating unit of PRASA Rail is responsible for the following:</p>
<ul>
    <li>Planning and managing day to day operations;</li>
    <li>Scheduling transport services;</li>
    <li>Maintaining assets (rolling stock)</li>
    <li>Collecting fares;</li>
    <li>Providing security for passengers; and</li>
    <li>Implementing operational safety plans.</li>
</ul>
<p>Metrorail South Africa provides a critical service with over 2.6 million passenger trips daily. It runs over 2300 train trips on a daily basis. It is the most affordable mode of transport that provides mobility to many South Africans.</p>

